a mixture of\noU am keros. He the chattering may\nk caused by too much kerosene\nTom i ...,pei Motor Company\nThe Tom Cooper Motor Company re\nports the following sale of Kord care\nfor the week ending March 26:\nFord touring cars to:\nK. D. Slough. Ardmvrt.\nJ. P. Dobbins, Mannsville.\nSid May. Ringling.\nFord delivery car to:\nFelker Hilton, city.\nFord Coupe to Donald M. Bretch, city.\nBrawley Molar Company\nThe Brawley Motor Company reports\nthe sale of un Essex touring car. e\npassenger. to J. W. Banks of Ardniore\nand a Hudsvn Speedster to M. M\nBramlett of Ardniore. recently.\nA two-horse team will haul a two\nton load over the average road at s\nlpv \"f ,'wo .\"tr\nhour a total\nhauj of 24 miles for an eight-hour\nday. In the same time a motor truck\nwill haul the same load a distance of\n136 miles. At the end of a year the\ntruck would gain 33.600 miles on the\ntram.\nThere is little excuse for the loss of\nlife and Ohe frightful Injuries received\nut railroad crossings. Automobile drv\ntrs lake Inexcusable chances aiW In\nnocent passengers suffer for it. The\ndriver may know his own speed, but\nI he has BO way of knowing the speed\nof the approaching train. While it may\nI be half-mile uway when noticed. It wnly\ni takes a few seconds lo reach the cross\ning. Motor Briefs\nTom CVoper and Moss Patterson are j\nattending the automobile show In Fort\nWorth this week.\nTom Harris of the Harris Battery\ni Company spent Thursday and Friday\nof last week in oklalhoma City.\nA. K. Kraft of the Stroman MOtWI\nConporatlon is In Houston, Texas, on\nbusiness for the company. Mr. Kraft\nwill remain in Houston until the later\npart of this week when he will return\nto Arxlmorc\nThe Packard Motor far Company of\nDetroit, MlcUi., hits a representative of\nthe Technical Service Department of\nthe Packard factory, who haa been\nSTEPHENS\nSALIENT SIX MOTOR CARS\nThe outstanding point of superiority in the Stepliens\nMutur is the fuel system originated by Strphrnx engineers\nand found only in tin- Stephens Salirnt Six. Here is the\nsecret of its rare combination of power and economy.\nIm close, high-mounted carburetor feeds the gas directly\nagainst the vaporizing wall heated by the exhaust from\ntht two center cylinders. The manifold is built Into the\ncylinder head, forming a smooth chamber that feeds per\nfectly vaporized, heated gag, evenly to the cylinders.\nGas so prepared explodes faster and burns completely,\ndelivering the greatest mileage to the gallon of gasoline,\nand pnabling the motor to handle low grade fuels wi'h\nout difficulty a solution of the problem of poor gasoline.\nThis feature, found only in this motor, combined with\nproven engineering throughout, makes the Stephens\nSalient Six a car of great power, flexibility, economy and\nreliability.\nStroman Motors Corporation\n224 West Main Ardmore, OkU\nNEWS\ngiving- special instruction to the me\nchanics vf the Guy Harris Motor Com\npany during the pjt week.\nK. .T. Stroman has returned from Dun\ncan where he spent several days. Mr\nStroman is president of the Stroman\nMotors Corporation.\nP. M. Brtgano Of the Stroman Mo\ntors Corporation spent Thursday in\nHeaidtton on business.\nJ. P. Brawley of the Brawley Mo-\nLiterally tearing great holes througSi\nthe atmosphere. Otto Walker crowned\nhimself king of motorcycle speed dem.\none by shattering four worlds records I\nat Fresno. California, recently. He did i\nbetter than 100 miles per hour In four\nruces. He holds the following \"compe-\ntltlon\" records: One mile. 33 2-5 see\nonds, or 107. TS miles per h.ur; ten miles\n.V4.V or 103.44 miles ner hour; fifteen\nmiles. S;37 L'-j, or 104.37 miles per hour; J is said to eliminate uric acid by stimu\nli nd fifty miles 3-5, or 101.43 miles! lating the kidneys to normal Action,\nper hour\nPresKlent Jackson rode horseback In\nresidential inauitural parade. All\nthe other presidents used carriages In\ntheir correspotidintt trips from the Cap\nitol to the While Houge. President